11 May 2010 16:12






Yes…eek! A Thing From The Future (or someone's future, at least). I thought it had a good enough hook to write it up, even though I know "stuff from the future" is pretty much a discredited trope around here. Enough people said they liked the concept in the chat/forum for me to go with it…totally expected a few down votes, since I know some folks here believe we have enough stuff from the future, especially from new writers.

Good point, thunderbird…I am going to add something to the partial report that came with the object to imply that it was more powerful wherever it was sent from than it appears to be here. Trying to balance the too explicit vs. too vague aspect has been difficult, since both lead to "not creepy enough". It's definitely not Keter here (and is only Euclid because no one is quite sure of the extent of its powers).








